4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would propose an amendment to the
6 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, relating to Henry
7 County, to authorize a qualified taxpayer 65 years of
8 age or older to claim a senior property tax assessment
9 for real property owned in the county under certain
10 conditions.
11
12
13 A BILL
14 TO BE ENTITLED
15 AN ACT
16
17 To propose an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
18 of 2022, relating to Henry County, to authorize a qualified
19 taxpayer 65 years of age or older to claim a senior property
20 tax assessment for real property owned in the county under
21 certain conditions.
22 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
23 Section 1. The following amendment to the Constitution
24 of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
25 PROPOSED AMENDMENT
26 (a) In Henry County, an individual 65 years of age or
27 older may claim a senior property tax assessment for ad
28 valorem tax purposes on real property located in the county
Page 1

valorem tax purposes on real property located in the county
HB460 INTRODUCED
29 which is owned by the individual, classified as single-family
30 owner-occupied residential property, and used and assessed as
31 the principal place of residence of the individual for not
32 less than 10 years immediately prior to the tax year for which
33 the individual first claims the senior property tax
34 assessment. The senior property tax assessment shall freeze
35 the assessed value of the property for the year immediately
36 prior to claiming the assessment.
37 (b) The following provisions shall apply to the
38 individual claiming the senior property tax assessment:
39 (1) The taxpayer shall continue to receive the senior
40 property tax assessment as long as the taxpayer continues to
41 use the property as his or her principal place of residence.
42 (2) The individual shall continue to be eligible to
43 claim a homestead exemption and any other exemption authorized
44 by law on the property.
45 (3) The property shall continue to be subject to any
46 millage rate changes on the property.
47 (4) The assessed value of any additions to the property
48 after claiming the senior property tax assessment shall be
49 added to the assessed value of the property and subject to ad
50 valorem tax based on the increase in the assessed value of the
51 addition after the taxpayer claims the senior property tax
52 assessment.
53 (5) This assessment may be claimed beginning October 1,
54 2027.
55 (6) This assessment must be claimed in writing with the
56 Henry County Revenue Commissioner between October 1 and
Page 2

Henry County Revenue Commissioner between October 1 and
