57 December 31.
58 Upon ratification of this constitutional amendment, the
59 Code Commissioner shall number and place this amendment as
60 appropriate in the constitution omitting this instructional
61 paragraph and may make the following nonsubstantive revisions:
62 change capitalization, hierarchy, spelling, and punctuation
63 for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
64 grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
65 internal or external citations and cross-references; harmonize
66 language; and translate effective dates.
67 END PROPOSED AMENDMENT
68 Section 2. An election upon the proposed amendment
69 shall be held in accordance with Sections 284, 284.01, and 285
70 of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, and the election laws
71 of this state. The appropriate election official shall assign
72 a ballot number for the proposed constitutional amendment on
73 the election ballot and shall set forth the following
74 description of the substance or subject matter of the proposed
75 constitutional amendment:
76 "Relating to Henry County, proposing an amendment to
77 the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, to authorize a qualified
78 taxpayer 65 years of age or older to claim a senior property
79 tax assessment for real property under certain conditions.
80 Proposed by Act ____."
81 This description shall be followed by the following
82 language:
83 "Yes( ) No( )."
84 Section 3. The proposed amendment shall become valid as
